Pet Adoption Platform – Complete System Documentation
1. INTRODUCTION
This document provides a complete description of the Pet Adoption Platform.

The main objective of the system is to help users find adoptable pets near their location

and complete the adoption process in a secure and structured manner.

2. ACTORS
User: Searches pets, views nearby animals, and submits adoption requests.

Shelter: Creates animal posts and manages adoption requests.

Administrator: Monitors listings and manages system integrity.

External Map Service: Provides user location data.

Notification Service: Sends email and SMS notifications.

3. USE CASE SCENARIOS
USE CASE: View Nearby Animals

Actor: User

Preconditions:

- User is on the main page.

- Location service is available.

 

Main Flow:

1. User selects View Animal Posts.

2. System displays all active posts.

3. User selects View Nearby Animals.

4. System requests location permission.

5. User grants permission.

6. System retrieves location from Map Service.

7. System filters posts by distance.

8. System displays nearby animals.

 

Postconditions:

- Nearby animals are displayed correctly.

 

USE CASE: Send Adoption Request

Actor: User

Preconditions:

- User is logged in.

- Selected post is active.

 

Main Flow:

1. User opens animal post.

2. User clicks Adopt This Pet.

3. System displays request form.

4. User submits request.

5. System validates data.

6. System saves request as Pending.

7. System notifies Shelter.

 

Postconditions:

- Request saved and visible to Shelter.

 

4. SEQUENCE DIAGRAMS – EXPLANATION
Sequence Diagram: View Nearby Animals

- User requests animal posts.

- System requests location permission.

- Map Service returns coordinates.

- System filters and displays nearby animals.

 

Sequence Diagram: Send Adoption Request

- User selects animal post.

- System verifies login.

- User submits adoption request.

- System saves request.

- Notification Service alerts Shelter.

 

Sequence Diagram: Approve or Reject Request

- Shelter reviews adoption requests.

- Shelter approves or rejects request.

- System updates request status.

- Notification Service notifies User.

 

